The rooftop, barren and desolate, somehow reminds me of <i>that</i> world.[r]
Its emptiness feels strangely familiar, but I don't think about it too hard.[r]
I head for the edge of the roof, making sure to avoid the cigarette butts under my feet; the rooftop is popular with smokers.[l][r]
Standing by the railing I reopen the email, my phone trembling ever so slightly as I punch in her number with sweaty hands.[r]
I tap the call button.[l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

